├── _auth/            # Authentication routes
│   ├── signin.tsx    # Sign in page
│   └── signup.tsx    # Sign up page
└── _public/          # Public routes
    └── index.tsx     # Public home page
```

## Library Organization

### 1. Core Library

The core library contains shared code used across features:

```sh
lib/
├── client/           # Client-side utilities
├── server/           # Server-side utilities
│   ├── db/          # Database operations
│   └── middleware/  # Server middleware
└── shared/          # Shared utilities
    ├── constants/   # Shared constants
    ├── types/       # Shared types
    └── utils/       # Shared utilities
```

### 2. Feature Library

Each feature contains its own isolated logic:

- Client-side API and hooks
- Server functions
- Feature-specific types and schemas
- No direct database operations (use core library)

## Best Practices

### 1. Code Organization

- Keep features self-contained
- Use clear, consistent naming
- Follow established patterns
- Maintain proper separation
- Use proper imports

### 2. Feature Development

- Start with shared types
- Build from bottom up
- Test at each level
- Document APIs
- Consider reusability

### 3. Code Sharing

- Share through core lib
- Keep dependencies clean
- Use proper abstractions
- Document shared code
- Version shared code

### 4. Performance

- Code split by feature
- Lazy load components
- Optimize imports
- Monitor bundle size
- Cache appropriately

